mcqs.question:
What will be the output of the following code?

int x = 10;
int *ptr = &x;
cout << *ptr << endl;

Consider the following code:

int arr[] = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};
int *ptr = arr;
ptr++;
cout << *ptr << endl;

What is the output?

What does the following code print?

int a[5] = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
int *p = a;
cout << *(p + 2) << endl;

What will happen when the following code is executed?

int *ptr = new int(50);
cout << *ptr << endl;
delete ptr;
cout << *ptr << endl;

Given the following code:

void modify(int *&ref) {
    ref = new int(100);
}

int main() {
    int *ptr = new int(50);
    modify(ptr);
    cout << *ptr << endl;
    return 0;
}

What is the output and why?
